</sense> <sense n="2" xml:id="D2"> <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la"><quote> hariolus </quote></cit>, <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la"><quote> divinus </quote></cit>, <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la"><quote> fatidicus </quote></cit>, <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la"><quote> magus </quote></cit> (cfr. <foreign xml:lang="ar">كَاهِنٌ</foreign>): <foreign xml:lang="gez">ውእቱ፡ ይገብር፡ ግብረ፡ ሥራይ፡ ወዘማርያት፡</foreign> <ref cRef="2 Par." loc="33,6">2 Par. 33,6</ref>; <foreign xml:lang="grc">ἐγγαστριμύθοι</foreign> <foreign xml:lang="gez">ማርያን፡</foreign> <ref cRef="1 Par." loc="10,13">1 Par. 10,13</ref>; <foreign xml:lang="gez">ማርያን፡ ወሰብአ፡ ሰገል፡</foreign> <foreign xml:lang="grc">μάγοι Ξαλδαῖοι Γαζαρηνοί</foreign> <ref cRef="Dan." loc="5,7">Dan. 5,7</ref>; <ref cRef="Did." loc="35 ">Did. 35 </ref>al.; <ref cRef="M.M." loc=" f. 314">M.M.  f. 314</ref> [Hanc vocem quondam in <bibl><ptr target="bm:Dillmann1857Gramm"/>gramm.</bibl> § 47; <bibl><ptr target="bm:Dillmann1857Gramm"/>gramm.</bibl> § 114,c; <bibl><ptr target="bm:Dillmann1857Gramm"/>gramm.</bibl> § 138,2 ad radicem <foreign xml:lang="gez">ርእየ፡</foreign> retuli, et <foreign xml:lang="gez">ማሪ፡</foreign>, e <foreign xml:lang="gez">መርኢ፡</foreign> vel <foreign xml:lang="gez">መርእይ፡</foreign> contractum, proprie <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la"><quote> monstratorem </quote></cit> i.e. <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la"><quote> interpretem </quote></cit> arcanorum vel <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la"><quote> hierophantem </quote></cit> significare esistimavi; sed postquam <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la"><quote> sacrificuli </quote></cit> notionem antiquitus potiorem fuisse cognovi, hoc etymon addubitaverim]. 
